    <!-- About Section -->
    <section id="about" class="text-center about">
      <div class="container-fluid content-section">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
                <h2 style="text-align:center">About the
                Seminar</h2>
                <p>The ECE Industry Interaction Seminar
                (IIS@ECE) is an initiative of
                the <a href="www.ece.iisc.ernet.in"
                target="_blank">Department of Electrical
                Communication Engineering</a> (ECE) at
                the <a href="www.iisc.ernet.in"
                target="_blank">Indian Institute of
                Science</a> (IISc) to encourage interaction
                between the vibrant tech industry of
                Bangalore and the researchers at the
                IISc. The city of Bangalore, revered as
                the tech capital of India, has seen
                unprecedented growth in tech startups and
                tech development centers. The IISc,
                located at the heart of Bangalore, is one of
                the oldest technical institutes of India, with
		a long standing tradition of excellence
                in research and innovation. IIS@ECE provides
                a forum for an informal interaction between the
                researchers of IISc and the technology
                developers of Bangalore. Every month a
                distinguished speaker from the industry will
                visit the ECE department and present a
                technical problem that interests their
                company. This will be followed by a
                discussion with the audience, a student
                roundtable, and of course, coffee in the
                ECE hut. We invite everyone to come and
                share ideas or a cup of coffee with the tech
                leaders of Bangalore in the lush green ECE
                department! 
		</p>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Download Section -->
    <section id="talks" class="content-section text-center talks-section">
      <div class="container-fluid">
                <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
                    <h2 class="talks-section-title">Upcoming and Past Talks</h2>
<div class="row">
		      <div  class="talk-block col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"
			    style="word-wrap:break-word;">

		      <p style="text-align:center;"><b> Systems R&amp;D in Tech Start-ups: Opportunities and Challenges.</b></p>
		       <img class="img-responsive img-center hidden-xs hidden-mobile"
		       src="img/speaker4.png"  style="float:left; padding-right:20px;"></img>
		       
		       <img class="img-responsive img-center visible-xs visible-mobile"
		       src="img/speaker4.png" style="margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto"></img>		     		 
		      <b>Who?</b> Ramu Srinivasaiah, Founder &amp; Director at Lekha Wireless<br />
  		      <b>When?</b> 4.00pm on 1st April, 2016 (Friday)<br />		      
		      <b>Where?</b> Golden Jubilee Hall, ECE Department<br />
		      <b>What?</b> In a tech start-up, once the vision has been conceived, system modeling and performance analysis of candidate algorithms and methods are carried out. However, simulations  go through constant changes at every stage of the design and development process. A change in the later stages of development is often expensive and time consuming. In this context, I will talk about few best practices for innovation which can help reduce  the product development cycle.


		     	      <span class="more">
				More ...
			      </span>		      
			      <div style="display:none">
				<br />
				<b> About the Speaker</b><br />
Ramu Srinivasaiah is the Founder and the Director of Lekha Wireless. He comes with 18 years of experience in wired and Wireless communication and has expertise in voice band modems, fax, ADSL modems, WiMAX and LTE technologies. Prior
to becoming an entrepreneur Ramu Srinivasaiah has worked for Encore
software, an Indian startup company, Centillium communication, a US
based semiconductor company, Navini Networks, a US based OEM company
and Cisco Systems. His current responsibilities at Lekha Wireless include businesses development, driving innovation, customer interaction, building and managing competent engineering teams and delivery of technology products.

				 <br/><br />	

<b> About the Company</b><br />
Lekha Wireless is a self-funded Indian startup. It is a company with
technology focus and has registered growth year after year. They are
team of more than 60 engineers with highly competent engineering
skills ranging from hardware to software and functionally ranging from
RF to networks. Lekha  has licensed its data link and embedded
technology to OEMs and has developed a vault of turn key solutions and
IPs over years. The company is in the process of taking these turnkey
solutions to devices which meets the compliance requirements of end
users. Lekha's ACT link solution is one such initiative which is IP
based point to point and point to multi point COFDM link. Lekha has
built these modems with algorithms that can take care of deployment
challenges which are completely different from typical commercial
networks. It has seen great traction from the defense R &amp;D and
end user communities. Also, Lekha has developed a Test and Measurement
product called WaveGuru for LTE technology which it is delivering to
customers.<br/> 
The next generation ACT link will be based on LTE technology and the
company's R&amp; D is working towards it.
 <br/><br /> 


 
				
				<span class="less">
				Less ...
				</span>
 
			      </div>

		      </div>
		    </div>
                    <br /><br />
 
<div class="row">
		      <div  class="talk-block col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"
			    style="word-wrap:break-word;">

		      <p style="text-align:center;"><b> Science and Technology Challenges in Healthcare Analytics</b></p>
		       <img class="img-responsive img-center hidden-xs hidden-mobile"
		       src="img/speaker3ii.png"  style="float:left; padding-right:20px;"></img>
		       
		       <img class="img-responsive img-center visible-xs visible-mobile"
		       src="img/speaker3i.png" style="margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto"></img>		     		 
		       <b>Who?</b> <i>We have two speakers this time!</i> <br/>Arun Rajagopalan, Director of Data Science and <br />Raghu Venkat, Director of R&amp D center at Evive Health <br />
		      <b>When?</b> 5:00 pm on 19th February 2016 (Friday)<br />		      
		      <b>Where?</b> Golden Jubilee Hall, ECE Department<br />
		      <b>What?</b> 
In health care, science and technology are deeply intertwined. In this talk, we focus on a few challenges that we handle on these two fronts. We have infrastructure and software challenges as well as data science and behavioral science puzzles to solve on a daily basis. We present examples of each and our solutions.
			      <span class="more">
				More ...
			      </span>		      
			      <div style="display:none">
				<br />
				<b> About the Speakers</b><br />
<i>Arun Rajagopalan</i> is the Director of Data Science at Evive Health. Prior to this, he was the Director of Research at Deep Value, an US based algorithmic trading firm. He has focused on data science in different domains from his graduate school days - materials informatics, crystallographic databases, high frequency equity market data, and now health care. <br />

Arun has a B.Tech. in Metallurgy from IIT Madras, India and a Ph.D. in Materials Science from Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, Troy, New York, USA. He was a guest researcher at National Institute of Standards and Technology, Gaithersburg, Maryland as part of his post-doctoral research. <br /> <br />

<i>Raghu Venkat</i> oversees Evive Health's R&D centre and has over 16 years of consulting experience. He primarily  programmed in the Real time applications with a focus on delivering testable software.<br />

Throughout his career, Raghu Venkat has served as an Advisor / Technical Consultant to large Fortune 500 companies, Stock exchanges (CME, CBOE) & insurance industry particularly related to real time computing.

				 <br/><br />	

<b> About the Company</b><br />
Based in Chicago and Bengaluru, and founded in 2007, Evive Health is the industry innovator in health care engagement in USA. Through personalized, timely communications, Evive Health works with some of the world's largest companies to increase employee adherence, health and wellness, and reduce costs. Since its inception, Evive has helped engage more than 7 million people across 50 states using advanced analytics and rules engines to deliver personalized messages by direct or digital media.<br />
We are a passionate team of data analysts, software engineers, creative designers, and healthcare professionals developing and delivering tools that help people take action on their health. At Evive Health, we believe that people will make the right decisions in health and financial wellbeing if they're given the right information, at the right time, in the right way. That's why we build personalized health and wealth tools that equip people with the information they need, and empower them to take action. <br />

Our solutions include: 
<ul>
<li> Open enrollment and plan selection </li>
<li> Preventive and chronic care decisions </li>
<li> Provider and cost decisions </li>
<li> Participation and outcomes-based personalized incentives </li>
</ul>
 <br/><br /> 


 
				
				<span class="less">
				Less ...
				</span>
 
			      </div>

		      </div>
		    </div>


		   <br /><br />



 <div class="row">
		      <div  class="talk-block col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"
			    style="word-wrap:break-word;">

		      <p style="text-align:center;"><b> Wi-Fi: A practitioner’s perspective</b></p>
		       <img class="img-responsive img-center hidden-xs hidden-mobile"
		       src="img/speaker2.png"  style="float:left; padding-right:20px;"></img>
		       
		       <img class="img-responsive img-center visible-xs visible-mobile"
		       src="img/speaker2.png" style="margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto"></img>		     		 
		      <b>Who?</b> Pravin Bhagwat, CTO Mojo Networks<br />		      		  		      <b>When?</b> 3:00pm on 29th January 2016 (Friday)<br />		      
		      <b>Where?</b> Golden Jubilee Hall, ECE Department<br />
		      <b>What?</b> 
		      In this talk, I’ll share perspective on Wi-Fi performance from a practitioner's viewpoint.  How users of Wi-Fi measure performance? What matters to them the most? Using many real life case studies, I’ll highlight several engineering issues (often overlooked in theoretical analysis) which have the first order effect on overall system performance. 
			      <span class="more">
				More ...
			      </span>		      
			      <div style="display:none">
				<br />
				<b> About the Speaker</b><br />
Pravin Bhagwat is an entrepreneur and a wireless security researcher. He is Co-founder and CTO of Mojo Networks -- a provider of highly scalable and secure cloud-managed Wi-Fi solutions. Mojo Networks has built a world class engineering team in Pune which is successfully launching ‘first-of-its-kind’ Cloud managed Wi-Fi products in the global market.<br />
Prior to starting his entrepreneurial career, Pravin was a lead researcher at AT&amp T Research and IBM Thomas J. Watson Research Center, New York where he was a member of MobileIP, Wi-Fi and Bluetooth research teams. He also served as a visiting faculty member at computer science department, IIT Kanpur. Pravin also has 16 patents to his credit.<br />
For the past three years, Pravin has also been experimenting with a couple of non-tech ideas, such as leading a community level green/recycling initiative, jumpstarting an eco-restoration project near Pune and making a feature film length documentary. Pravin has B.Tech. in Computer Science from IIT Kanpur, India and MS/PhD in computer science from the University of Maryland, College Park, USA.
 
				 <br/><br />	

<b> About the Company</b><br />
Mojo Networks is redefining the modern Wi-Fi platform. Imagine the scalability to set up thousands of access points with a few clicks, all from your smartphone. Envision an Internet experience that engages users with your business to drive results. Stay secure on the same Wi-Fi cloud powering Fortune 500s, Global 2000s and high levels of government. And enjoy the cost savings of a cloud-first solution without the pricey markup of proprietary hardware. Welcome to the era of prolific connectivity. Founded in 2003, Mojo Networks (formerly known as AirTight Networks), serves customers in the Fortune 500, Global 2000 and large carriers around the world.

 <br/><br /> 


 
				
